            <title>[JCR-196] jcr:like() does not scale well on large value ranges</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-196</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>There are two major issues with the current WildcardQuery implementation:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
1) A wildcard expression is restricted to match at most 1024 terms, otherwise a TooManyClauses exception is thrown. Similar to the RangeQuery issue: &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-111&quot; title=&quot;org.apache.lucene.search.BooleanQuery$TooManyClauses when using &amp;#39;&amp;gt;&amp;#39; operator&quot;&gt;&lt;strike&gt;JCR-111&lt;/strike&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
2) The enumeration over the terms that match the wildcard pattern is slow</description>
